<paragraph blockId="16.[151,684,290,1115]" pageId="16" pageNumber="71">
Slender terrestrial herb 
<quantity box="[486,607,290,317]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="16" pageNumber="71" unit="cm" value="16.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="14.0">14-18 cm</quantity>
high. Tubers 2, up to 2 × 
<quantity box="[407,495,321,348]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="16" pageNumber="71" unit="cm" value="1.2">1.2 cm</quantity>
, ovoid, villous. Leaves 2, in the upper half of the stem, alternate, 3.5-5 × 
<quantity box="[312,416,382,409]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="71" unit="cm" value="0.75" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5-1 cm</quantity>
, narrowly lanceolate or linear-lanceolate, forming a funnel-shaped sheath at the base that clasps the stem. Inflorescence 1-3-flowered; bracts leafy, 18-32 × 
<quantity box="[151,245,505,532]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3-4 mm</quantity>
. Flowers with green sepals, veined with pink, petals pink; pedicel and ovary 
<quantity box="[589,684,536,563]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8-9 mm</quantity>
long. Dorsal sepal 
<quantity box="[368,437,566,593]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
long, linear, forming with the petals a broad, very concave hood c. 
<quantity box="[178,245,628,655]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
high and 
