<quantity box="[196,266,658,685]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
, joined near the base, falcate, the tips curling in, each with a sac-like spur in the basal half. Petals hyaline. Lip erect part joined to the column for most of its length with only a short free part; appendage 3-lobed; mid-lobe 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="4.25" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.5">3.5- 5 mm</quantity>
