<quantity box="[528,619,904,931]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2-3 mm</quantity>
long, linear-oblong, glabrous or with short papillae on the upper surface, arching and curving to the side, narrower than the mid-lobe and twisted at the tips. Rostellum lobes very broad and thick with hyaline, spathulate arms, twisted and geniculate at the base. — 
